    <div class="description-contents">
      <p>Homo sapiens rules the world because it is the only animal
      that can believe in things that exist purely in its own
      imagination, such as gods, states, money and human
      rights.</p>
      <p>Starting from this provocative idea, Sapiens goes on to
      retell the history of our species from a completely fresh
      perspective. It explains that money is the most pluralistic
      system of mutual trust ever devised; that capitalism is the
      most successful religion ever invented; that the treatment of
      animals ...</p>
